WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:08.359
(CAMERA SLATE)

2
00:00:09.919 --> 00:00:11.400
Common mark

3
00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.039
(FOOTSTEPS)

4
00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:16.000
Okay... I'm set.

5
00:00:16.719 --> 00:00:17.679
- Set.

6
00:00:18.079 --> 00:00:21.079
- Camera A set.

7
00:00:21.079 --> 00:00:25.160
(PIANO MUSIC)

8
00:00:36.159 --> 00:00:39.479
So, can you tell me a bit about yourself

9
00:00:39.479 --> 00:00:42.119
and how you communicate?

10
00:00:48.039 --> 00:00:49.679
Hi, I'm Gretta,

11
00:00:49.679 --> 00:00:53.280
I'm a 31 year old woman from Western Sydney.

12
00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:57.159
As I am a non-verbal woman with severe Cerebral palsy,

13
00:00:57.159 --> 00:01:01.320
my primary method of communication is using my iPad,

14
00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:03.960
which I operate with my nose.

15
00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:33.519
I'm Quang.

16
00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:38.040
I'm 40 years old.

17
00:01:38.760 --> 00:01:44.760
I communicate...

18
00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:49.640
with my mobile phone,

19
00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:52.159
laptop,

20
00:01:52.159 --> 00:01:55.200
text to speech.

21
00:01:55.599 --> 00:02:00.319
Why do you think communication is so important?

22
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:01.479
As a non-verbal woman,

23
00:03:01.479 --> 00:03:05.240
I feel that communication is very important.

24
00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:07.000
This is not only for safety

25
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:09.960
and getting someone's point across,

26
00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:12.080
it is also a key factor for them

27
00:03:12.080 --> 00:03:16.159
to express their personality and intelligence.

28
00:03:16.159 --> 00:03:19.039
Personally, this importance of communication

29
00:03:19.039 --> 00:03:22.319
was visible when I first went on social media,

30
00:03:22.319 --> 00:03:26.560
as I felt I could express myself properly.

31
00:03:29.039 --> 00:03:33.360
(TYPING)

32
00:03:35.919 --> 00:03:37.919
(TEXT ALERT)

33
00:03:47.599 --> 00:03:50.199
And what opportunities

34
00:03:50.199 --> 00:03:53.960
do you think communication opens up for you?

35
00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:24.519
(GENTLE PIANO MUSIC)

36
00:04:38.519 --> 00:04:39.120
For me,

37
00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:42.480
it took many years to find my most suitable

38
00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:45.439
and efficient method of communication.

39
00:04:45.439 --> 00:04:50.079
When I discovered how easy it was to use my iPad,

40
00:04:50.079 --> 00:04:53.639
both of my online and offline worlds opened up for me

41
00:04:53.639 --> 00:04:57.000
as I could express my views, opinions,

42
00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:01.480
intelligence and personality to my full potential.

43
00:05:03.279 --> 00:05:05.000
(TEXT ALERT)

44
00:05:14.800 --> 00:05:16.480
(TEXT ALERT)

45
00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:29.040
How free do you feel to express yourself, and why?

46
00:05:41.079 --> 00:05:45.399
I feel completely free by being able to fully communicate

47
00:05:45.399 --> 00:05:49.560
because I have every opportunity to express myself

48
00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:52.439
and really develop my personality

49
00:05:52.439 --> 00:05:54.120
despite my disability.

50
00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:54.879
(SIGHS)

51
00:06:40.959 --> 00:06:43.680
And what are some of the barriers

52
00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:48.560
that you face to communication?

53
00:06:53.920 --> 00:06:56.560
The main barrier with my communication,

54
00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:59.279
which I feel I somewhat struggle with,

55
00:06:59.279 --> 00:07:02.199
is the time I take to prepare responses.

56
00:07:02.199 --> 00:07:04.360
I mainly recognise this

57
00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:07.240
when I am talking within a group of people

58
00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:10.199
as I struggle to keep up with conversation.

59
00:07:10.199 --> 00:07:13.000
This barrier is particularly present

60
00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:16.000
when I am having a heated discussion with someone

61
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.240
or when people are impatient with the wait time.

62
00:07:20.839 --> 00:07:23.959
(EXPERIMENTAL STRING MUSIC)

63
00:08:02.519 --> 00:08:04.000
(TYPING)

64
00:08:04.519 --> 00:08:06.519
(TEXT ALERT)

65
00:08:08.519 --> 00:08:10.519
(TEXT ALERT)

66
00:08:21.839 --> 00:08:24.279
EMILY: Can you describe a time in your life

67
00:08:24.279 --> 00:08:27.600
when it was difficult for you to communicate,

68
00:08:27.600 --> 00:08:30.480
and sort of how that made you feel?

69
00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:36.519
Although I can't remember one particular moment,

70
00:08:36.519 --> 00:08:38.720
I do feel that I really start

71
00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:42.039
to get frustrated with my communication

72
00:08:42.039 --> 00:08:44.080
when I'm really upset with someone

73
00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:47.720
and want to just yell at them to get my point across

74
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:49.639
so I tend to just yell,

75
00:08:49.639 --> 00:08:53.200
and then become embarrassed that I look immature.

76
00:09:51.279 --> 00:09:53.200
(TEXT ALERT)

77
00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:01.879
(TEXT ALERT)

78
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:05.600
I actually feel that people with disabilities

79
00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:08.200
make normal mistakes everybody make,

80
00:11:08.200 --> 00:11:11.840
people are more likely to have opinions about it

81
00:11:11.840 --> 00:11:16.600
and analyse it as a behaviour that needs to be fixed.

82
00:11:16.600 --> 00:11:20.039
Now, can you describe a time in your life

83
00:11:20.039 --> 00:11:24.039
when it was made easier for you to communicate?

84
00:11:31.679 --> 00:11:33.399
(TEXT ALERT)

85
00:11:33.399 --> 00:11:36.519
(UPLIFTING MUSIC)

86
00:11:39.120 --> 00:11:40.840
(TEXT ALERT)

87
00:11:50.159 --> 00:11:52.000
I think when I was at uni,

88
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:55.240
I felt that I was able to communicate freely,

89
00:11:55.240 --> 00:11:57.360
and all of the lecturers and students

90
00:11:57.360 --> 00:12:00.639
understood my communication needs.

91
00:12:00.639 --> 00:12:02.639
In tutorials and lectures

92
00:12:02.639 --> 00:12:05.840
I always made sure I said at least one thing,

93
00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:08.080
so that the people around me knew

94
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:12.120
that my disability didn't affect my intellect.

95
00:13:29.600 --> 00:13:31.080
(TEXT ALERT)

96
00:13:34.679 --> 00:13:36.159
(TEXT ALERT)

97
00:13:41.639 --> 00:13:44.440
What would you say to someone who might be worried

98
00:13:44.440 --> 00:13:47.919
about getting communication wrong?

99
00:13:57.399 --> 00:14:00.960
I always say it's better to be honest with me.

100
00:14:00.960 --> 00:14:02.559
When you don't understand

101
00:14:02.559 --> 00:14:06.120
what the communicator is trying to express,

102
00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:08.879
don't pretend that you understand.

103
00:14:08.879 --> 00:14:12.600
Instead, just ask the communicator to continue trying

104
00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:16.039
until they feel like they have gotten their message across.

105
00:14:16.039 --> 00:14:18.159
When people give me this time,

106
00:14:18.159 --> 00:14:20.639
I feel empowered and respected.

107
00:14:30.840 --> 00:14:32.559
(TEXT ALERT)

108
00:14:37.840 --> 00:14:41.639
And what are some of the other things that people can do

109
00:14:41.639 --> 00:14:44.879
to be an effective communicator?

110
00:14:53.159 --> 00:14:54.879
(TEXT ALERT)

111
00:14:57.519 --> 00:14:59.240
(TEXT ALERT)

112
00:15:03.080 --> 00:15:04.799
(TEXT ALERT)

113
00:15:09.360 --> 00:15:12.440
(PIANO &amp; SYNTH MUSIC)

114
00:15:50.120 --> 00:15:51.720
Be patient and remember

115
00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:54.240
most people that you're communicating with

116
00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:56.440
want the best for you.

117
00:15:56.440 --> 00:15:59.120
Is there anything else you'd like to add?

118
00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:19.200
(TEXT ALERT)

119
00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:25.639
(MUSIC BUILDS)

120
00:16:25.639 --> 00:16:28.120
It's so amazing and extremely important

121
00:16:28.120 --> 00:16:31.279
that these types of materials are coming out.

122
00:16:33.360 --> 00:16:37.799
(MUSIC BUILDS)

123
00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:53.360
(MUSIC SWELLS)

124
00:16:56.759 --> 00:17:00.679
(PIANO)

